Again, no clue. I'm not on social media.

@Barry Ancona
That's why I called it messy rather than wrong. Maybe it's an inside/too close thing. Everyone I've known associated with the show calls it Quintet for disambiguation. Programs have listed it as Tonight Quintet, Tonight (Quintet), and Tonight (Quintet and Chorus). There may be other variations as well.

Lucky you to have seen the original!

@Rome
If you're loving Sunday then you're already loving a larger puzzle at roughly Wednesday difficulty. Steve L is right, go to the archives to hone your skills.

Group solving can be fun; others bring different wheelhouses and perspectives. There are some online options, but why not see if you can get some of your friends interested? Game night!

